<h1 class=3D"center">Binary Number System</h1>=20


<p>A binary number is made up of only <b>0</b>s and <b>1</b>s.</p>

	<table style=3D"border: 0; margin:auto;">
		<tbody><tr style=3D"text-align:center;">
			<td>=20
<div class=3D"huge">110100</div></td>
		</tr>
		<tr style=3D"text-align:center;">
			<td>Example of a binary Number</td>
		</tr>
	</tbody></table>=20
<p>There is no 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7, 8 or 9 in binary!</p>=20
<p>Binary numbers have many uses in mathematics and beyond.</p>=20
<p class=3D"center"><img src=3D"https://www.mathsisfun.com/numbers/images/d=
igital-world.jpg" alt=3D"digital world" height=3D"144" width=3D"360"><br>
In fact the digital world uses <a href=3D"https://www.mathsisfun.com/binary=
-digits.html">binary digits</a>.</p>=20


<h2>How do we Count using Binary?</h2>=20

<p>It is just like counting in decimal except we reach 10 much sooner.</p>=
=20
<div class=3D"simple">

	<table style=3D"border: 0; margin:auto;">
		<tbody><tr>
			<td class=3D"large center">Binary</td>
			<td>&nbsp;</td>
			<td>&nbsp;</td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
			<td class=3D"large center">0</td>
			<td>&nbsp;</td>
			<td>We start at 0</td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
			<td class=3D"large center">1</td>
			<td>&nbsp;</td>
			<td>Then 1</td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
			<td class=3D"large center">???</td>
			<td>&nbsp;</td>
			<td>But then there is no symbol for 2 ... what do we do?</td>
		</tr>
	</tbody></table>=20
</div>=20

<div class=3D"center80">
<p class=3D"larger">Well how do we count in Decimal?</p>

	<table style=3D"border: 0; margin:auto;">
		<tbody><tr>
			<td style=3D"width:20px;">&nbsp;</td>
			<td class=3D"large" style=3D"text-align: right;">0</td>
			<td>&nbsp;</td>
			<td>Start at 0</td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
			<td>&nbsp;</td>
			<td class=3D"large" style=3D"text-align: right;">...</td>
			<td>&nbsp;</td>
			<td>Count 1,2,3,4,5,6,7,8, and then...</td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
			<td>&nbsp;</td>
			<td class=3D"large" style=3D"text-align: right;">9</td>
			<td>&nbsp;</td>
			<td>This is the <b>last digit</b> in Decimal</td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
			<td>&nbsp;</td>
			<td class=3D"large" style=3D"text-align: right;"><span class=3D"hilite">=
1</span>0</td>
			<td>&nbsp;</td>
			<td>So we start back at 0 again, but add <span class=3D"hilite">1</span>=
 on the left</td>
		</tr>
	</tbody></table>
</div>=20

<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>The same thing  is done in binary ...</p>=20
<div class=3D"simple">

	<table style=3D"border: 0; margin:auto;">
		<tbody><tr>
			<td>&nbsp;</td>
			<td class=3D"large center">Binary</td>
			<td>&nbsp;</td>
			<td>&nbsp;</td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
			<td>&nbsp;</td>
			<td class=3D"large" style=3D"text-align: right;">0</td>
			<td>&nbsp;</td>
			<td>Start at 0</td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
			<td>=E2=80=A2</td>
			<td class=3D"large" style=3D"text-align: right;">1</td>
			<td>&nbsp;</td>
			<td>Then 1</td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
			<td>=E2=80=A2=E2=80=A2</td>
			<td class=3D"large" style=3D"text-align: right;"><span class=3D"hilite">=
1</span>0</td>
			<td>&nbsp;</td>
			<td>Now start back at 0 again, but <b>add <span class=3D"hilite">1</span=
> on the left</b></td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
			<td>=E2=80=A2=E2=80=A2=E2=80=A2</td>
			<td class=3D"large" style=3D"text-align: right;">11</td>
			<td>&nbsp;</td>
			<td>1 more</td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
			<td>=E2=80=A2=E2=80=A2=E2=80=A2=E2=80=A2</td>
			<td class=3D"large" style=3D"text-align: right;">???</td>
			<td>&nbsp;</td>
			<td>But NOW what ... ?</td>
		</tr>
	</tbody></table>=20
</div>

<div class=3D"center80">
<p class=3D"larger">What happens in  Decimal?</p>

	<table style=3D"border: 0; margin:auto;">
		<tbody><tr>
			<td class=3D"large center">&nbsp;</td>
			<td class=3D"large" style=3D"text-align: right;">99</td>
			<td>&nbsp;</td>
			<td>When we run out of digits,  we ...</td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
			<td class=3D"large center">&nbsp;</td>
			<td class=3D"large" style=3D"text-align: right;"><span class=3D"hilite">=
1</span>00</td>
			<td>&nbsp;</td>
			<td>... start back at 0 again, but add <span class=3D"hilite">1</span> o=
n the left<br>
</td>
		</tr>
	</tbody></table>
</div>=20

<p>&nbsp;</p>=20
<p>And that is what we do in binary ...</p>=20
<div class=3D"simple">

	<table style=3D"border: 0; margin:auto;">
		<tbody><tr>
			<td>&nbsp;</td>
			<td class=3D"large center">Binary</td>
			<td>&nbsp;</td>
			<td>&nbsp;</td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
			<td>&nbsp;</td>
			<td class=3D"large" style=3D"text-align: right;">0</td>
			<td>&nbsp;</td>
			<td>Start at 0</td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
			<td>=E2=80=A2</td>
			<td class=3D"large" style=3D"text-align: right;">1</td>
			<td>&nbsp;</td>
			<td>Then 1</td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
			<td>=E2=80=A2=E2=80=A2</td>
			<td class=3D"large" style=3D"text-align: right;"><span class=3D"hilite">=
1</span>0</td>
			<td>&nbsp;</td>
			<td>Start back at 0 again, but add 1 on the left</td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
			<td>=E2=80=A2=E2=80=A2=E2=80=A2</td>
			<td class=3D"large" style=3D"text-align: right;">11</td>
			<td>&nbsp;</td>
			<td>&nbsp;</td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
			<td>=E2=80=A2=E2=80=A2=E2=80=A2=E2=80=A2</td>
			<td class=3D"large" style=3D"text-align: right;"><span class=3D"hilite">=
1</span>00</td>
			<td>&nbsp;</td>
			<td>start back at 0 again, and add one to the number on the left...<br>
... but that number is already at 1 so it also goes back to 0 ...<br>
... and 1 is added to the <i>next position</i> on the left</td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
			<td>=E2=80=A2=E2=80=A2=E2=80=A2=E2=80=A2=E2=80=A2</td>
			<td class=3D"large" style=3D"text-align: right;">101</td>
			<td>&nbsp;</td>
			<td>&nbsp;</td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
			<td>=E2=80=A2=E2=80=A2=E2=80=A2=E2=80=A2=E2=80=A2=E2=80=A2</td>
			<td class=3D"large" style=3D"text-align: right;">110</td>
			<td>&nbsp;</td>
			<td>&nbsp;</td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
			<td>=E2=80=A2=E2=80=A2=E2=80=A2=E2=80=A2=E2=80=A2=E2=80=A2=E2=80=A2</td>
			<td class=3D"large" style=3D"text-align: right;">111</td>
			<td>&nbsp;</td>
			<td>&nbsp;</td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
			<td>=E2=80=A2=E2=80=A2=E2=80=A2=E2=80=A2=E2=80=A2=E2=80=A2=E2=80=A2=E2=
=80=A2</td>
			<td class=3D"large" style=3D"text-align: right;"><span class=3D"hilite">=
1</span>000</td>
			<td>&nbsp;</td>
			<td>Start back at 0 again (for all 3 digits),<br>
add 1 on the left</td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
			<td>=E2=80=A2=E2=80=A2=E2=80=A2=E2=80=A2=E2=80=A2=E2=80=A2=E2=80=A2=E2=
=80=A2=E2=80=A2</td>
			<td class=3D"large" style=3D"text-align: right;">1001</td>
			<td>&nbsp;</td>
			<td>And so on!</td>
		</tr>
	</tbody></table>=20
</div>=20

<p>&nbsp;</p>=20
<p>See how it is done in this little demonstration (press play button):</p>=
=20

